# Diagram/Whiteboard Widget (P2 #7)

**Priority:** P2 (Medium)
**Estimated Time:** 10-12 hours
**Status:** Planning
**Created:** 2025-11-26

---

## Overview

Add an interactive diagram/whiteboard widget to the dashboard using Excalidraw for local-first, hand-drawn style diagramming. This enables users to create flowcharts, diagrams, mind maps, and freeform sketches directly in Neuman Brain without external tools.

## Problem Statement

Users currently have:
- **No visual diagramming** - Can't create flowcharts, diagrams, or visual planning
- **External tool dependency** - Must use Draw.io, Excalidraw web, or Miro separately
- **No integration** - Diagrams can't link to notes/tasks
- **Context switching** - Breaks flow when planning visually

**Use Cases:**
- **Developers:** Architecture diagrams, flowcharts, system design
- **Project managers:** Process flows, org charts, project planning
- **Students:** Mind maps, concept diagrams, study notes
- **Designers:** Wireframes, user flows, brainstorming

**Why Excalidraw:**
- ✅ Local-first (matches Neuman Brain philosophy)
- ✅ Hand-drawn aesthetic (friendly, approachable)
- ✅ Open source MIT license
- ✅ TypeScript-first with React integration
- ✅ Embeddable as React component
- ✅ Supports export to PNG/SVG
- ✅ IndexedDB persistence built-in
- ✅ No server required
- ✅ Actively maintained

