## Technical Approach

### Library: Excalidraw

**Installation:**
```bash
npm install @excalidraw/excalidraw
```

**Bundle Size:**
- ~180KB gzipped (widget lazy-loaded)
- No initial bundle impact
- Acceptable for diagramming features

**Integration Pattern:**
```tsx
import { Excalidraw } from "@excalidraw/excalidraw";

function DiagramWidget() {
  return (
    <div style={{ height: "500px" }}>
      <Excalidraw
        onChange={(elements, appState, files) => {
          // Auto-save to Zustand store
        }}
        initialData={{
          elements: savedElements,
          appState: savedAppState,
          files: savedFiles,
        }}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Architecture

**Data Flow:**
```
User Interaction → Excalidraw Component → onChange → useDiagramsStore → IndexedDB
                                                   ↓
                                          debounced auto-save
```

**Components:**
- `DiagramWidgetCard.tsx` - Dashboard widget card with thumbnail
- `DiagramModal.tsx` - Full-screen/modal diagram editor
- `DiagramList.tsx` - List of saved diagrams
- `DiagramEditor.tsx` - Excalidraw wrapper with Neuman Brain styling

**Stores:**
- `src/stores/useDiagramsStore.ts` - Diagram management (CRUD, persistence)

**Types:**
- `src/types/diagrams.ts` - Diagram metadata, Excalidraw data

### Data Model

**Diagram:**
```typescript
interface Diagram {
  id: string; // UUID
  title: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  thumbnail?: string; // Base64 PNG for preview

  // Excalidraw data
  elements: ExcalidrawElement[]; // Shapes, arrows, text
  appState: Partial<AppState>; // Zoom, grid, theme
  files: BinaryFiles; // Embedded images

  // Metadata
  tags?: string[];
  linkedNotes?: string[]; // Note IDs (Phase 2)
  linkedTasks?: string[]; // Task IDs (Phase 2)
}
```

**Store:**
```typescript
interface DiagramsStore {
  diagrams: Record<string, Diagram>;

  // CRUD
  createDiagram: (title: string) => string;
  updateDiagram: (id: string, data: Partial<Diagram>) => void;
  deleteDiagram: (id: string) => void;
  getDiagram: (id: string) => Diagram | undefined;

  // Utilities
  exportDiagramAsPNG: (id: string) => Promise<Blob>;
  exportDiagramAsSVG: (id: string) => Promise<string>;
  importDiagram: (file: File) => Promise<string>;
}
```

